                .ignoringDisable(true));
</code></pre>
<p>However, when we add vision measurements, that overrides the new pose we set, understandably.</p>
<p>I am trying to think of a good way to make it so that we can zero the heading to the driver’s liking, but also have an accurate position on the field.</p>
<p>Can someone please point me in the right direction?</p>
<p>I think the appropriate thing to do is to check the alliance color and invert the controls based on what alliance we are. However, I don’t know if that is the right way to do things.</p>
<p>Do anyone else have this issue and how did you solve it?</p>
<p><strong>Additional Info</strong><br>
We are using AdvantagKit Swerve TalonFX template mixed with the AdvantageKit Vision template and Photonvision</p>
