user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3552930,"name":"Justin Buist","username":"Justin_Buist","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/c77e96/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-10T16:59:12.964Z","cooked":"<p>We sort of love the side effect of that. It no longer matters how we boot up the robot, just spin it 360 on our field and it’ll orient itself. Drivers will burn through a whole battery without ever setting their yaw.</p>
<p>So, I agree with your solution. It’s the same as ours. Just check query the Driverstation to see what side of the field you’re on. If on red invert the x and y controls of the joystick.</p>
<p>Caveat: If you set the robot up somewhere with AprilTags that are on the field but not in the right spots your bot will be horribly confused as to where it’s pointed. We ran into this on a practice field where all the elements were close. Our robot’s back camera could see a barge tag that was in the ‘wrong’ spot compared to the AprilTag in front of it. Soo… we had to cover up the back camera for the driver to have any real control.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2025-03-10T16:59:12.964Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":58,"readers_count":57,"score":16.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":494990,"topic_slug":"vision-overrides-heading-zero-ing","display_username":"Justin Buist","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24678,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/vision-overrides-heading-zero-ing/494990/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3553089,"name":"Chadfrom7226","username":"Chadfrom7226","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/chadfrom7226/{size}/113429_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-10T18:39:59.082Z","cooked":"<p>I might make a toggleable mode where it can either be manually set or updated with apriltags and play around to see what I like</p>
